observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management, through the concerned offices, agreed to implement/observe the following measurers:
The BAC, assisted by the TWG, conduct thorough post qualification ensure that the projects are awarded to the bidders who really have the technical, legal, and financial capacity to implement the contract, hence, unnecessary delay can be avoided;
The Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Planning Officer conduct judicious and meticulous planning and assessment of the project prior to procurement and implementation;
The Municipal Mayor, through the Municipal Accountant, impose the liquidated damages as mandated by RA No. 9184;
The Municipal Accountant take-up the necessary adjusting entries on the effects of erroneously treating the progress payments of the still ongoing projects as already PPE account; and
The concerned official/s responsible for the preparation and review of the Quarterly Report of Government PPAs ensure that the submitted report reflect the actual status of the projects.

The Municipal Mayor instruct the concerned official/personnel to:

submit an authenticated copy of the JVA between the Municipality of Cordova and the CCGRI, including its Annexes B and C;

submit an authenticated copy of the documents related to the procedures and processes for the selection of the project proponent as mentioned in Sangguniang Bayan (SB) Resolution No. 296-13;

fully account and collect any share of revenue entitled to the Municipality under the JVA; and

submit information on the expected completion date of the Cordova Eco-tourism Center and Fisherfolks’ Livelihood Hub project.

